    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Here are some elements\r\n\r\n- The escrow only supported Eth, not ERC20. This looked like a limitation that could lead to errors, and lost tokens\r\n- This indirectly affect PullPayment, that relies on the escrow\r\n- The usage of this contract is extremelly low, and its only used by advanced users that can import it from 4.9 or reimplement it\r\n- That is code we ahve to maintain, provide security for, ...\r\n\r\nIn the end, we did not fell like it was a good idea to carry that code to 5.0, and commit to maintain it until at least 6.0. Depending on the need / request, we may reintroduce it in a better way in an upcomming minor version.\r\n\r\nIf your are missing it, please open an issue documenting your needs so we can discuss the best way to address them, and the right feature-set for a new version of this design.",
